{"active_answer": "spongy and springy", "active_index": 55, "active_question": "How can jute rope feel after getting wet and drying out?", "audit_index": 1, "decision": "edit", "document_sha256": "b316fd1a708dcb7688d44826496dd58b8c06d20b9c01d8daa73e99e7704abc53", "edited_answer": "spongy and springy", "edited_question": "After wet jute rope dries, how does Anatomie Studio say its tightened twist may make the rope feel?", "fact_id": "fact-da15b630db4ec0ed79cf", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 55, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The revised question preserves the useful care warning while making the tightened-twist mechanism and source explicit.", "reason_code": "clarify_wet_jute_texture_mechanism", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 3, "bare_answer_points": 2, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 11, "risk_score": 2, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_144932682af9c846.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "3e77a59322805eb277e5cc7e86fb5592e71b889b3c95197c2c401d2533d2c1c8", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "The first thing you should know is that you generally don’t want to get your jute ropes wet. Anyone who’s had a glass or water spilled on their ropes will tell you that the ropes swell up, and the twist tightens making the ropes feel spongy and springy when they dry out. Note: if this does even happen to you, make sure you dry the ropes under tension to help them return to their original form. This is actually one of the factors that makes dyed ropes more expensive. While you could just chuck your set of jute ropes in the washing machine for an intensive wash and spin cycle we wouldn’t recommend it.", "support_evidence_sha256": "9120e03cb72f2fca8866db25b48d1cf68de4e0b58d3d74c6ed43e259c93b214e", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/blog/cleaning-jute-rope-after-sexy-time"}
{"active_answer": "edge play", "active_index": 62, "active_question": "How does Anatomie Studio classify suspension in its studio safety rules?", "audit_index": 2, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "1d66ad91809311443abe27e549840e5436c510a1e66fe1e2cefd6d68c078d3c4", "fact_id": "fact-eb477d063e72bae0adb8", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 62, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The concise attributed answer accurately preserves Anatomie Studio’s explicit classification of suspension as risky edge play.", "reason_code": "retain_explicit_suspension_risk_classification", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 2, "bare_answer_points": 5, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 1, "question_tokens": 11, "risk_score": 8, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_27ecdd4d7c9a5560.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "1f968e0d0b2428eab259dfd3c291f58483c5384b6eebca1fa2505ce9b39f23af", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "Use of the points is reserved for experienced people. If you see people suspending, they have very likely completed our courses or have received tuition here or elsewhere. Suspension is edge play. It is risky. Do not endanger yourself or others by suspending before you are ready. Respect when the owners or staff ask you to stop suspending. Come ask us about classes if you’d like to learn!", "support_evidence_sha256": "a07e00f26e2cb3814f406f168cf8d5ae46070d72a782ccc3286915f45d455022", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/etiquette-and-consent"}
{"active_answer": "no", "active_index": 110, "active_question": "In Anatomie Studio's consent guidance, how should mixed messages be interpreted?", "audit_index": 3, "decision": "edit", "document_sha256": "1d66ad91809311443abe27e549840e5436c510a1e66fe1e2cefd6d68c078d3c4", "edited_answer": "“no”", "edited_question": "How does Anatomie Studio say mixed consent messages should be interpreted?", "fact_id": "fact-069a861dbb2bea9e47ca", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 110, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The revised answer uses the source’s quoted term and the question states the consent context naturally.", "reason_code": "repair_mixed_messages_answer_rendering", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 1, "bare_answer_points": 6, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 11, "risk_score": 6, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_27ecdd4d7c9a5560.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "1f968e0d0b2428eab259dfd3c291f58483c5384b6eebca1fa2505ce9b39f23af", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "– Mixed messages mean “no.”", "support_evidence_sha256": "8cba5acb0c4322e5cdfbb72163134064c7c1278cc930e24c32fdcb5daeac485e", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/etiquette-and-consent"}
{"active_answer": "negotiation", "active_index": 190, "active_question": "What does Anatomie Studio call conversations in which people give and receive enthusiastic, active consent for activities and touching?", "audit_index": 4, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "1d66ad91809311443abe27e549840e5436c510a1e66fe1e2cefd6d68c078d3c4", "fact_id": "fact-372357c6d61a3f8b6ce6", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 190, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The question already supplies the studio and consent context, and the one-word answer is the exact term defined by the source.", "reason_code": "retain_clear_negotiation_definition", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 1, "bare_answer_points": 6, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 19, "risk_score": 6, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_27ecdd4d7c9a5560.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "1f968e0d0b2428eab259dfd3c291f58483c5384b6eebca1fa2505ce9b39f23af", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "Give and receive enthusiastic, active consent for activities and any kind of touching. We call these conversations ‘negotiation’.", "support_evidence_sha256": "e2178b6d98943647ea2b0691c55d8d382847022f5263030f627e60f09d331477", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/etiquette-and-consent"}
{"active_answer": "informed consent", "active_index": 288, "active_question": "What must all parties be able to give when deciding how ropes will be used?", "audit_index": 5, "decision": "edit", "document_sha256": "b316fd1a708dcb7688d44826496dd58b8c06d20b9c01d8daa73e99e7704abc53", "edited_answer": "informed consent", "edited_question": "In Anatomie Studio’s rope-hygiene guidance, what must all parties be able to give before deciding how rope will be used?", "fact_id": "fact-f7e802bf0b2759290dc6", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 288, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The revised question makes clear that this consent requirement concerns hygiene choices about shared or intimate rope use.", "reason_code": "add_hygiene_context_to_informed_consent", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 2, "bare_answer_points": 5, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 15, "risk_score": 5, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_144932682af9c846.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "3e77a59322805eb277e5cc7e86fb5592e71b889b3c95197c2c401d2533d2c1c8", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "Whatever you decide, it’s important to make sure all parties are able to give informed consent. Personal boundaries and individual risk profiles are very different and just because you’re ok (or not) with something, doesn’t mean it will be the same for your partner(s).", "support_evidence_sha256": "57e877db16a165f844e4792fa4692ae6a6c188a9dd7928d1deba15e8edf6f103", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/blog/cleaning-jute-rope-after-sexy-time"}
{"active_answer": "don’t proceed", "active_index": 329, "active_question": "What should someone do if they doubt whether a partner is verbally and physically enthusiastic?", "audit_index": 6, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "1d66ad91809311443abe27e549840e5436c510a1e66fe1e2cefd6d68c078d3c4", "fact_id": "fact-a3833a3bcbe7d6dc8400", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 329, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The existing question and answer form a direct, actionable rule for responding to doubt about a partner’s enthusiasm.", "reason_code": "retain_actionable_enthusiasm_check", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 2, "bare_answer_points": 5, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 1, "question_tokens": 15, "risk_score": 8, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_27ecdd4d7c9a5560.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "1f968e0d0b2428eab259dfd3c291f58483c5384b6eebca1fa2505ce9b39f23af", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "Is your partner enthusiastic verbally and physically? Check in. If you have doubts, don’t proceed.", "support_evidence_sha256": "0cba6077c01c4ab22328c1cc2fac417632fefbb5c8457e40ea2060b268846eef", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/etiquette-and-consent"}
{"active_answer": "the rigger", "active_index": 380, "active_question": "When a rope model becomes non-verbal, who does Anatomie Studio say has the immediate responsibility to check in?", "audit_index": 7, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "396e550c0110696f10dbdd4ccad5750d0c2b4fa46baf84a4095d550588dd8b3a", "fact_id": "fact-97d52aa2d87dadfd8226", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 380, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The attributed row clearly assigns the immediate check-in responsibility when the model cannot communicate verbally.", "reason_code": "retain_nonverbal_model_check_in_responsibility", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 2, "bare_answer_points": 5, "named_person_trivia_points": 6, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 18, "risk_score": 11, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_9749de0eb1ff4ef3.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "2ce0036f18ab2fbb48a91470e56fa9105557b89744b329509898b7315cf9812d", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "Committing to take joint responsibility is a great way to relieve some of the pressure. However, it’s important to note that models can go non-verbal in rope, or simply sink into a space in which communication means they lose their headspace. In this case the immediate responsibility will fall to the rigger to check in.", "support_evidence_sha256": "1280256a6ec3d20767dcd96b1c29782c2223d0f9ee64f43a5d8fe8cbefcb11f8", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/blog/should-we-use-safe-words-in-shibari"}
{"active_answer": "freezing", "active_index": 462, "active_question": "Which response does Anatomie Studio's consent guidance say must not be treated as consent?", "audit_index": 8, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "1d66ad91809311443abe27e549840e5436c510a1e66fe1e2cefd6d68c078d3c4", "fact_id": "fact-03cbcf694e260c90a1bf", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 462, "baseline_rows": 537, "baseline_sha256": "22e81a31c5ec4531a22d6ba3de67c0d986b07bab19088cc27d08164d7167c249", "prior_context_merit_review": true}, "reason": "The concise answer directly teaches that a freeze response must not be treated as consent.", "reason_code": "retain_freeze_response_consent_rule", "review_pass": "anatomie_consent_hygiene_and_checkin_reaudit", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v65", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 1, "bare_answer_points": 6, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 14, "risk_score": 6, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v65", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_27ecdd4d7c9a5560.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "1f968e0d0b2428eab259dfd3c291f58483c5384b6eebca1fa2505ce9b39f23af", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "– Respect “no” (“no” is a complete sentence). Silence is not consent, freezing is not consent.", "support_evidence_sha256": "885faa8350d2d9b969fd7bdb580c53a894eba337af513e8793f69cd133b9a7b1", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/etiquette-and-consent"}
